No fewer than 64 persons were reported  injured as a petrol tanker exploded on Saturday in Kano. The incident happened at the Al-ihsan petrol station at Sharada in Kano Municipal Area of the state. Malam Saminu Abdullahi, spokesman of the Kano Fire Service, confirmed the incident in a statement yesterday. Abdullahi said out of the injured victims, eight fire service personnel were involved, adding that no life was lost. The tanker was offloading petroleum products at the filling station when the incident occurred, he said. “The victims were taken to Murtala Muhammed Specialist Hospital and Nassarawa Hospital,” he said. 